          ['Jumper list', 'Wire endpoints by row/rail', 'Manual wiring order'],
          ['Validation notes', 'Warnings and edge cases', 'Final pre-build sanity check']
        ]
      },
      {
        id: 'step-4-download-or-share-the-result',
        title: 'Step 4: Download or Share the Result',
        illustrationSummary:
          'This export panel simulation previews PNG, SVG, and JSON output from the same layout. Users can switch format tabs and see what details each export keeps. It supports handoff for classrooms, makerspaces, or team documentation.',
        purpose:
          'Content purpose: explain delivery options and help users choose the right output for fabrication notes or collaboration.',
        diagramTitle: 'Export and Share Panel',
        diagramSteps: [
          {
            label: 'Preview',
            detail: 'Inspect final layout details before export.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Export',
            detail: 'Select PNG/SVG for visual output or JSON for editable project transfer.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Share',
            detail: 'Send files to teammates or include in documentation workflows.'
          }
        ],
        tableCaption: 'Step 4 format selection',
        tableHeaders: ['Format', 'Best Use', 'Includes'],
        tableRows: [
          ['PNG', 'Slides, quick sharing', 'Flat visual layout'],
          ['SVG', 'Scalable docs and print', 'Vector geometry and labels'],
          ['JSON', 'Project iteration and reload', 'Structured nets and metadata']
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    main: {
      id: 'schematic-to-breadboard-examples',
      title: '3. Schematic to Breadboard Examples',
      illustrationSummary:
        'This example selector is an interactive gallery where users swap among multiple circuits and compare schematic, mapping, and breadboard views. Each switch keeps the same UI so differences in complexity are obvious. It accelerates learning through pattern recognition.',
