          'This interactive rail-mapping game asks users to assign VCC and GND rails correctly, then tests with continuity hints. Wrong picks generate instant short/open warnings. It builds reliable rail discipline before hardware testing.',
        purpose:
          'Content purpose: reduce power-rail mistakes that cause immediate failures or unsafe shorts.',
        diagramTitle: 'Power and Ground Rail Checker',
        diagramSteps: [
          {
            label: 'Label',
            detail: 'Label both positive and ground rails explicitly before wiring.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Connect',
            detail: 'Attach each power net to the correct rail and verify polarity.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Test',
            detail: 'Run continuity and short checks between rails and load paths.'
          }
        ],
        tableCaption: 'Power/GND error prevention',
        tableHeaders: ['Check', 'Why It Matters', 'Pass Condition'],
        tableRows: [
          ['Rail polarity', 'Prevents reverse power', 'VCC/GND correctly assigned'],
          ['Rail continuity', 'Ensures stable distribution', 'Consistent rail voltage'],
          ['Short guard', 'Prevents component damage', 'No direct VCC-GND short']
        ]
      },
      {
        id: 'mistake-2-reversed-component-orientation',
        title: 'Mistake 2: Reversed Component Orientation',
