        tableCaption: 'Orientation-critical components',
        tableHeaders: ['Component', 'Orientation Rule', 'Risk if Reversed'],
        tableRows: [
          ['LED/diode', 'Anode/cathode must align', 'No conduction or damage'],
          ['Electrolytic cap', 'Positive/negative polarity respected', 'Leakage or failure'],
          ['Transistor', 'Correct B/C/E orientation', 'Switch stage fails']
        ]
      },
      {
        id: 'mistake-3-floating-connections',
        title: 'Mistake 3: Floating Connections',
        illustrationSummary:
          'This continuity heatmap marks each required net as connected or floating. Users drag missing jumpers until every net passes the check. It provides a practical pre-power checklist for hidden opens.',
        purpose:
          'Content purpose: ensure full net completion so circuits do not fail due to unconnected nodes.',
        diagramTitle: 'Floating Net Heatmap',
        diagramSteps: [
          {
            label: 'Scan',
            detail: 'Scan all required nets and mark unresolved nodes.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Patch',
            detail: 'Insert missing jumper links to restore connectivity.'
          },
          {
            label: 'Finalize',
            detail: 'Re-run continuity checks until all nets report connected.'
          }
